<font color="#FF0000">THE REAL TOPIC IS?</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec  4 21:31:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet <br>
Evidently you are speaking once again without taking the time to read the past posts. Much healing, much dialog and many important issues have been intensely discussed with several points of views reflected on these threads over the past few months. The laughter and human emotions shared were all part of the pain there and now. <br><br>
Go back and look them over. No one dominated the threads, PTSD and other sobering issues were discussed openly and with great insight and thoughtful sharing. That is until the so called psychologist intervened with his sickness, then you will find I often backed off and everyone else responded to his rude and very offensive remarks. I agree with Marc that when I responded I did so with intensity, but they are words coined from my commitment to honor those I knew who died in battle, and those who suffered much after their return to a sorry world unworthy of their commitment to protect them at a great cost.<br><br>
The dialog has been between veterans and non-vets as well as those who protested the war. The discussions have not been token or spoken under the banner of deceitfulness or shallow coverings.  <br><br>
A wealth of information about Vietnam veterans who fought the war with respect and honor can now be found here. What they did then and what they are doing today. It is all here and it is so very real. Thoughts are shared with deep insight as only those who were there and who faced the battles of Nam as well as the silence and disrespect upon our return. Its all here. <br><br>
It is a different site today, one which does not support the blame everything on the government and embrace those who spit on our face mentality. We’re not here to embrace each other then talk, but to talk before that honor can be given. All that other fluff around our discussions can be found when the thoughts shared became too intense. <br><br>
As a marine who will not visit this site anymore told me just this pass week-end, there were some heavy stuff being discussed and I could only visit it once in a while because of that, they took time for me to digest and contemplate but they were good thoughts that I needed. But he also mentioned that when he saw the abuse by that “doc” he didn’t want that. Why subject yourself to that all over again.<br><br>
I did not come here to be abused by an individual who is not what he claims to be, how many e-mail messages did you get from him before you couldn't stand it any longer and decided to post the note above?<br><br>
I and others will no longer address him or post on the threads he starts, so now there is a e-mail war going on behind the scenes.  <br><br>
Still censorship that protects him because of what he posted is not understandable by anyone willing to hear the truth. <br>

